{
  "_comment": "Editable config for Layer 2 (Fever Signal). Search-term groups + the India state/UT list. Change freely; no code edits needed. Values are Google-Trends-style RELATIVE interest, normalized 0-100 (never absolute counts).",
  "model_version": "L2-0.1.0",
  "geo": "IN",
  "lookback_weeks": 12,

  "groups": [
    {
      "key": "febrile",
      "label": "Fever",
      "disease": "General febrile illness",
      "headline": true,
      "terms": ["fever", "viral fever", "body ache", "high temperature"]
    },
    {
      "key": "dengue",
      "label": "Dengue",
      "disease": "Dengue",
      "terms": ["dengue symptoms", "dengue test", "platelet count"]
    },
    {
      "key": "malaria",
      "label": "Malaria",
      "disease": "Malaria",
      "terms": ["malaria symptoms", "malaria test"]
    },
    {
      "key": "chikungunya",
      "label": "Chikungunya",
      "disease": "Chikungunya",
      "terms": ["chikungunya", "joint pain fever"]
    }
  ],

  "_states_comment": "India states + union territories. The `code` is the ISO 3166-2:IN sub-region code; verify it against the chosen real provider's geo codes before going live (Google Trends region codes can differ for a few entries). The mock provider keys on `name`.",
